* ./runner.py ./test/test_ftk_xul_two.py

ftk/dll.py:164: RuntimeWarning: memory leak in callback function.
	result = func(*args, **kwargs)

the bug is caused by ftk_xul_translate_text, it returns a new string object to
the ftk library, but the ftk library could not free the string object, so
the ctypes report a RuntimeWarning.

* ./runner.py demo/demo_draw.py

FtkError exception from ftk_widget_update in callback on_paint

the invoke sequence of on_paint:

ftk_window_idle_invalidate [win]
	ftk_window_disable_update [win]
	ftk_widget_paint [win]
		ftk_window_disable_update [win]
		ftk_widget_paint_self [win]
			ftk_widget_paint [painter]
				ftk_widget_paint_self [painter]
					on_paint [painter]
						ftk_widget_update [painter]
							check updated_disabled [win] ==> 2 ==> return RET_FAIL
		ftk_window_enable_update
	ftk_window_enable_update
